comments: After the pick, Johnson (NOP) and Valanciunas (MEM) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Anderson (MEM) is progressing when he receives the pass and gathers the ball on his left foot, while establishing his right as his pivot. He releases his dribble prior to lifting his pivot foot.
Valanciunas (MEM) could be deemed to be in the lane for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Bledsoe's (NOP) path and firms up on his left foot to absorb the contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Alexander-Walker's (NOP) path and absorbs the contact.
At the end of the drive, Alexander-Walker (NOP) trails Brooks (MEM) and incidental foot to foot contact occurs as he comes to a stop.

Alexander-Walker (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Morant (MEM) and cleanly pokes the ball loose. Morant is allowed to go into the backcourt to recover the ball and any ensuing contact with Ball (NOP) as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Bledsoe (NOP) legally contests Brooks' (MEM) jump shot attempt.
Hayes (NOP) reaches for the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm, which does not affect his ability to maintain full control of the ball and make his intended pass.
Ball (NOP) commits a take foul on Brooks (MEM).
Ball (NOP) swipes down and makes contact with Brooks' (MEM) wrist, which affects his ability to make his intended pass.
Marshall (NOP) commits a take foul on Anderson (MEM).
During the inbounds, Melton (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on Alexander-Walker (NOP) and cleanly deflects the pass away.
Hayes (NOP) is slightly late to establish himself in a screening position in Melton's (MEM) path and marginal contact occurs during the defensive switch.
